LEGISLATIVE BILL 803A
Introduced by von Gillern, 4.
Read first time March 26, 2026
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to appropriations; to appropriate funds to aid
2 in carrying out the provisions of Legislative Bill 803, One Hundred
3 Ninth Legislature, Second Session, 2026; and to declare an
4 emergency.
5 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
-1-

LB803A LB803A
2026 2026
1 Section 1. There is hereby appropriated (1) $235,157 from the
2 General Fund for FY2026-27 and (2) $111,400 from the General Fund for
3 FY2027-28 to the Department of Revenue, for Program 102, to aid in
4 carrying out the provisions of Legislative Bill 803, One Hundred Ninth
5 Legislature, Second Session, 2026.
6 Total expenditures for permanent and temporary salaries and per
7 diems from funds appropriated in this section shall not exceed $81,300
8 for FY2026-27 or $83,800 for FY2027-28.
9 Sec. 2. Since an emergency exists, this act takes effect when
10 passed and approved according to law.
